Here's a recommended structure for testing C# MCP tools with mocked HTTP dependencies:

**1. Abstract the HTTP client behind an interface:**

```csharp
// In your server project
public interface IApiClient
{
    Task<WeatherData> GetWeatherAsync(string city);
}

public class ApiClient : IApiClient
{
    private readonly HttpClient _http;
    public ApiClient(HttpClient http) => _http = http;
    public async Task<WeatherData> GetWeatherAsync(string city)
        => await _http.GetFromJsonAsync<WeatherData>($"/weather/{city}");
}
```

**2. Inject `IApiClient` into your tool class:**

```csharp
public class WeatherTool
{
    private readonly IApiClient _api;
    public WeatherTool(IApiClient api) => _api = api;

    [McpServerTool, Description("Get weather for a city")]
    public async Task<string> GetWeather(string city)
    {
        var data = await _api.GetWeatherAsync(city);
        return $"{data.TempF}°F, {data.Condition}";
    }
}
```

**3. Create the test project:**

```bash
dotnet new xunit -n MyMcpServer.Tests
cd MyMcpServer.Tests
dotnet add reference ../MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj
dotnet add package Moq
```

**4. Write tests with a mocked client:**

```csharp
public class WeatherToolTests
{
    [Fact]
    public async Task GetWeather_ReturnsFormattedString()
    {
        var mock = new Mock<IApiClient>();
        mock.Setup(c => c.GetWeatherAsync("Seattle"))
            .ReturnsAsync(new WeatherData { TempF = 55, Condition = "Cloudy" });

        var tool = new WeatherTool(mock.Object);

        var result = await tool.GetWeather("Seattle");

        Assert.Equal("55°F, Cloudy", result);
    }

    [Fact]
    public async Task GetWeather_WhenApiFails_ThrowsMeaningfulError()
    {
        var mock = new Mock<IApiClient>();
        mock.Setup(c => c.GetWeatherAsync(It.IsAny<string>()))
            .ThrowsAsync(new HttpRequestException("Service unavailable"));

        var tool = new WeatherTool(mock.Object);

        await Assert.ThrowsAsync<HttpRequestException>(
            () => tool.GetWeather("Nowhere"));
    }
}
```

**Key principles:**

| Layer | Technique |
|---|---|
| **Tool logic** | Inject `IApiClient`; test with Moq/NSubstitute |
| **HTTP serialization** | Test `ApiClient` with `MockHttpMessageHandler` (from `RichardSzalay.MockHttp`) |
| **Integration** | Use `WebApplicationFactory` or a real test server for end-to-end |

This keeps your tool tests fast and deterministic — no real network calls, and each layer is testable independently.
